us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFramePoint3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple3DBasics, FramePoint3DReadOnly, FrameTuple3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Point3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Point3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FramePoint3DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePoint3D

    public interface FixedFramePoint3DBasics
extends FramePoint3DReadOnly, FixedFrameTuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Point3DBasics
    Write and read interface for a 3D point expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this point is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Point3DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFramePoint3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on points occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FixedFramePoint3DBasics extends Point3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Point3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFramePoint3DBasics.
